#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:18
msgid "Writing Style Guide"
msgstr "Guida allo stile di scrittura"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:24
msgid "Goals"
msgstr "Obiettivi"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:27
msgid "User Focused"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:29
msgid "The manual shall be kept understandable by beginners to video editing."
msgstr ""
"Il manuale deve essere mantenuto comprensibile dai principianti al montaggio "
"video."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:33
msgid "Complete"
msgstr "Completo"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:35
msgid "All features, options and tools of **Kdenlive** should be described. The manual should provide information on what a feature is, its purpose, and how to use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:40
msgid "Concise"
msgstr "Conciso"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:42
msgid "Keep the text short and concise and relevant to the topic you describe."
msgstr ""
"Mantieni il testo breve, conciso e pertinente all'argomento che descrivi."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:46
msgid "Maintainable"
msgstr "Manutenibile"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:48
msgid "Write content that will not have to be redone the moment some small change is made in **Kdenlive**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:52
msgid "Content Guidelines"
msgstr "Linee guida sui contenuti"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:54
msgid "Use American English (e.g: modeling and not modelling, color and not colour) also for formatting numbers (e.g: 2,718.28 and not 2 718,28)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:56
msgid "Use spell checking."
msgstr "Utilizza il controllo ortografico."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:58
msgid "Take care about grammar, appropriate wording and use simple English."
msgstr ""
"Fai attenzione alla grammatica, alla formulazione appropriata e usa un "
"inglese semplice."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:60
msgid "Think of what could be interesting for a video editor."
msgstr "Pensa a cosa potrebbe essere interessante per un editor video."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:62
msgid "Describe in general and not in full depth, so you don't have to adapt the documentation with each new **Kdenlive** version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:64
msgid "Do not describe bugs, no actual state."
msgstr "Non descrivere bug, nessuno stato attuale."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:66
msgid "Including why or how an option might be useful. Example :ref:`sequence_advantage`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:68
msgid "If you are unsure about how a feature works, ask someone else or find out who developed it and ask them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:70
msgid "you can add comment (which is not shown in the HTML page, but useful for other editors): ``.. TODO, How to choose the correct output format and bit rate? Ask advanced user.``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:74
msgid "Style"
msgstr "Stile"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:76
msgid "Keep sentences short and clear, use verbs and less noun. Resulting in text that is easy to read, objective and to the point. Rule of thumb (but not only!): 20 words or 120 letters per sentence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:78
msgid "Be specific: Do not write *input device* when you mean the *mouse*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:80
msgid "Be entertaining: Each sentence describes something new."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:82
msgid "Use bold text to highlight: **Program names**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:84
msgid "Use italic text to emphasize: *Words or phrases as in general writing*, *Titles when referencing other works*, *The first use of an unfamiliar word*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:86
msgid "Combined Bold and Italic Text: In restructured text this is only possible with additional code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:90
msgid "Putting a definition first"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:97
#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:115
#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:131
msgid "better"
msgstr "migliore"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:104
msgid "Then explain what it does and then explain how you can use it. Example: :ref:`sequence`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:108
msgid "Avoiding the immediate repetition of the term"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:124
msgid "avoiding the “it is”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:140
msgid "Images"
msgstr "Immagini"

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:142
msgid "Only ``.. figure::`` should be used to place images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:144
msgid "Use the **Kdenlive** dark theme when making screenshots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:146
msgid "Use .webp for images."
msgstr "Usa .webp per le immagini."

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:148
msgid "Use animated .gif or .mp4 files if that explains the feature/task better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../get_involved/writing_style_guide.rst:150
msgid "Try to avoid having a lot of images. Use a single image that shows all of the relevant areas placed at the top of the section. Numbering the features and then explain the features in that order. Like this :ref:`example <project_tree>`."
msgstr ""

